news.title: Blackstone and Sattva Group file draft offer document for Rs 7,000 crore REIT IPO
news.para: Blackstone will hold a 55% equity stake in Knowledge Realty Trust, with Sattva Group retaining the remaining 45%. The REIT's projected net operating income (NOI) for FY26 is expected to be Rs 2,652 crore, rising to Rs 2,946 crore by FY27.

news.title: Birla Opus plans to expand portfolio and dealer network in FY26
news.para: Aditya Birla Group entered into the decorative paints segment in February 2024 and aims to have a double-digit share and generate a gross revenue of Rs 10,000 crore within 3 years of full-scale operations.

news.title: Lucknow development body to move NCLAT against Ansal API
news.para: National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) had admitted Ansal API for insolvency proceedings last week on an application filed by IL&FS Financial Services, one of the company’s financial creditors.

news.title: Chandigarh administration proposes significant increase in collector rates
news.para: The sharpest increase proposed is in the residential segment, particularly in the rural areas. In the sectoral grid of the city, the proposed growth in the collector rate ranges from 42% to 128%

news.title: Geberit expects construction sector in Europe to be stable in 2025
news.para: "Overall, the global economy will face considerable uncertainties in 2025," Geberit said. "These geopolitical and macroeconomic risks are leading to corresponding uncertainties in the building construction industry."

news.title: Ireland: Dalata Hotel Group explores potential sale, launches strategic review
news.para: The company said it had appointed Rothschild & Co as financial adviser in connection with the strategic review, adding that it is not in discussions with, or in receipt of an approach from any potential suitor.

news.title: Construction PMI in UK falls in February 2025
news.para: The all-sector PMI, which combines the services, manufacturing and construction sectors, fell to a 16-month low of 50.0 in February from 50.3 in January.

news.title: China considers ending price limit for local governments buying apartments: Report
news.para: The world's second-largest economy is dealing with prolonged property sector crisis with home prices expected to drop at a faster pace this year despite measures from the government.

news.title: Carpediem Capital invests Rs 100 crore in CorporatEdge
news.para: CorporatEdge plans to deploy Rs 350 crore in the next three years. It will unveil two centres, each spanning across 50,000 sq ft, in Q1 FY26 at World Trade Center (WTC) Nauroji Nagar, New Delhi, and Godrej Golf Course Road, Gurugram.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto drops 28.5% in February 2025
news.para: Seasonally adjusted sales were down 28.5% on a month-over-month basis to 4,326 units after climbing 12.4% in January. Compared to February 2024, sales were down 27.4%.

news.title: Nashik civic body issues notices to 2,000 property tax dodgers
news.para: So far, notices have been issued to over 2,000 defaulters, asking them to clear their tax dues within 15 days. The NMC has over 1.5 lakh property tax defaulters with dues over Rs 250 crore.

news.title: Two firms to set up global capability centres in Indore
news.para: Two enterprises have announced intentions to establish GCCs in Indore, pledging to generate approximately 40,500 new employment opportunities in the region.
